[
    {
        "content": "<p>The general issue for <code>SysmemFlush</code> (<a href=\"https://lore.kernel.org/rust-for-linux/20260409-fix-systemflush-v1-1-a1d6c968f17c@nvidia.com/\">https://lore.kernel.org/rust-for-linux/20260409-fix-systemflush-v1-1-a1d6c968f17c@nvidia.com/</a>) is that one resource depends on another resource and it needs to outlive its dependencies so <code>Drop</code> can still access it.</p>\n<p>I've done some experiments and I think something like this could work:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">std</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">marker</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">PhantomData</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">trait</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ForLt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Ty</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">l</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"cp\">#[doc(hidden)]</span>\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">ForLtImpl</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">F</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">F</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">mod</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nn\">internal</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">super</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">trait</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">WithLt</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">l</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Ty</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">lt</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">F</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">O</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">WithLt</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">lt</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ForLtImpl</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">F</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">F</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">FnOnce</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;'</span><span class=\"na\">lt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">())</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">O</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Ty</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">O</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">for</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">l</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">WithLt</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">l</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ForLt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Ty</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">l</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">as</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">WithLt</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">l</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">Ty</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"fm\">macro_rules!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">for_lt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"cp\">$lt</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"nc\">lifetime</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"cp\">$t</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">ty</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">ForLtImpl</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"cp\">$lt</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"cp\">$lt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">())</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"cp\">$t</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"cp\">$t</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">ty</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">ForLtImpl</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;'</span><span class=\"nb\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">())</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"cp\">$t</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">// All of the above to get higher-ranked lifetimes for types, not just trait bounds.</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Bar</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">SysmemFlush</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">(</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Bar</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">);</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Drop</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">SysmemFlush</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">drop</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"c1\">// Still have access to `bar`.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">DevResLt</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">ForLt</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"c1\">// Actually `T::Ty&lt;'a&gt;` for some `'a`</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">PhantomData</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">Ty</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"nb\">static</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">// Having driver core making sure `SysmemFlush` is dropped before dropping `bar`.</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Foo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">DevResLt</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">for_lt</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">SysmemFlush</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>cc <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"671004\">@Danilo Krummrich</span></p>",
        "id": 585215515,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1776093030
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm not sure how this would work, as it would result into something self-referential, no? I.e. a field of some struct would borrow from another field of that same struct.</p>\n<p>I came up with this [1] (obviously not final), but it should work fine.</p>\n<p>[1] <a href=\"https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/dakr/linux.git/log/?h=devres/chain\">https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/dakr/linux.git/log/?h=devres/chain</a></p>",
        "id": 585292124,
        "sender_full_name": "Danilo Krummrich",
        "timestamp": 1776119437
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It's not self-referential, to the struct itself it just reference something else. Your approach could work too, but it's only for <code>Drop</code>,  while this is supposed to be a general solution that allows all methods in the wrapped resources to reference its dependency</p>",
        "id": 585292349,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1776119607
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(Also, it would allow you to use Rust's native drop without additional traits)</p>",
        "id": 585292383,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1776119631
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If only drop is needed you could probably use with what I have above with something like:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">DevResInner</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">D</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">dep</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">D</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">T</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Send</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">DevresDrop</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">D</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">D</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Send</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Drop</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">DevResInner</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">D</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">drop</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">devres_drop</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">dep</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">DevRes</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">D</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">DevResLt</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">for_lt</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">DevResInner</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">D</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 585293879,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1776120478
    },
    {
        "content": "<blockquote>\n<p>It's not self-referential, to the struct itself it just reference something else.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Right, but a common use-case is that this struct and the thing it references is embedded within the same struct.</p>",
        "id": 585445713,
        "sender_full_name": "Danilo Krummrich",
        "timestamp": 1776177651
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But they'll be wrapped separately in <code>DevRes</code> containers?</p>",
        "id": 585445920,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1776177708
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Right, this should be fine then.</p>",
        "id": 585447223,
        "sender_full_name": "Danilo Krummrich",
        "timestamp": 1776178029
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Let me see what I can come up with.</p>",
        "id": 585447891,
        "sender_full_name": "Danilo Krummrich",
        "timestamp": 1776178194
    }
]